title: Djibouti gov't launches Africa's biggest free-trade zone
description:
Djibouti has broken ground for the first phase of Africa's biggest free-trade zone. The country is seeking to capitalise on its strategic position on one of the world's busiest trade routes. President Ismail Omar Gulleh launched the scheme that will also create jobs and build houses for his people. CGTN's Girum Chala reports from Djibouti.
